description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advert for Learning Disabilities Practice development Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 6/7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting new role for a learning disabilities registered nurse to become part of the education team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this fixed term role is to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the ongoing education and training specifically related to caring for people with learning disabilities autism of nurses midwives’&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with the Lead Nurse Learning Disabilities Nurse to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver a training plan for frontline clinical staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop coordinate, implement and evaluate the education programmes within Barts Health NHS Trust for this staff group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor effectiveness of the educational programme and make recommendations for the future&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be highly motivated and well organised, with an ability to communicate confidently and effectively at all levels&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will include working closely with, the trusts learning disability senior nurse , and other key stakeholders to develop strong working relationships and regional partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is offered initially on a fixed term contract or secondment until 31st March&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;winnie.george@nhs.net or patriciahandley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
